      "writtenOn": "2017-12-05T17:55:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I\u0027d go for retrying indefinitely because one should never have to restart monasca-api manually once influxdb is operational once more\n\nI don\u0027t think this is a good idea for several reasons.\n\n1. Indefinite waiting time will break many things with unproper error messages because in many places default timeout is 60 seconds. Afaik in a typical configuration Horizon waits for 60 seconds for reply from monasca AND the browser waits 60 seconds for reply from Horizon. Timeout errors are bad because we are not sure what happened to our action. It led to hardly-diagnosed errors in keystone some time ago.\n\nIt will also mean the panel in Horizon will be \"loading\" for $timeout seconds. Do we really want it?\n\n2. My expectation is that even if monasca-api fails to connect to influxdb on the first attempt, the first request after influxdb is up will spin up a new thread/process where the connection will be re-inited successfully. At least this is what i expect from a wsgi application.\n\nWhat do you think?",
      "parentUuid": "df87a7cf_216dd803",
      "revId": "f01eb3f0be4933176ac78c450397a066dbff688d",
      "serverId": "4a232e18-c5a9-48ee-94c0-e04e7cca6543",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "df87a7cf_ea9337a2",
        "filename": "monasca_api/common/repositories/influxdb/metrics_repository.py",
        "patchSetId": 1
